* BMAP phase-9 integration test: macros + literals + EQU + relocation together,
* exercising feature interactions the per-feature fixtures isolate.
*   - DBL is a macro whose body uses its #1 argument (an EQU'd absolute symbol);
*   - =5 is used inside the code twice (LDQ, ADQ) -> ONE deduped LITERALS word;
*   - STA START references a code label -> a section-0 relocation.
       OUNAME PROG9
DBL    MACRO
       LDA    #1
       ADA    #1
       ENDM
TWO    EQU    2
START  DBL    TWO
       LDQ    =5
       ADQ    =5
       STA    START
       END
